


3. Currency Selection for Cash Flow Visualization
Use Case Name: Select Currency for Visualization
Primary Actor: CFO
Goal: To allow the user to choose a specific currency to visualize the cash flows, either in original or converted EUR values.
Preconditions: The user has transaction data with multiple currencies.
Triggers: The CFO selects a currency from the dropdown.
Main Success Scenario:
The CFO selects the currency filter from the dashboard.
The system shows a list of currencies used in payments.
The CFO selects the desired currency or chooses EUR for conversion.
The system dynamically updates the cash flow visualization to show transactions in the selected currency.
Postconditions:
The cash flow visualization is displayed using the chosen currency.


4. Visualize Cash Flows by Company Division
Use Case Name: View Cash Flows by Company Division
Primary Actor: CFO
Goal: To enable users to visualize cash flows for different divisions within the company.
Preconditions: Division structure is provided.
Triggers: The CFO selects the company division filter.
Main Success Scenario:
The CFO selects the "Division" filter option.
The system provides a list of available divisions.
The CFO chooses a specific division or selects all divisions.
The system updates the visualization to display only the transactions for the selected division(s).
Postconditions:
The user views cash flows for a particular division or the entire company.



5. Filter Cash Flows by Specific Parameters
Use Case Name: Filter Cash Flows
Primary Actor: CFO
Goal: To allow users to filter cash flows based on different parameters such as time, currency, payment type, etc.
Preconditions: The user has uploaded transaction data.
Triggers: The CFO selects one or more filters from the filtering options.
Main Success Scenario:
The CFO selects specific filters (e.g., time period, currency, payment type).
The system retrieves the filtered data based on the selected parameters.
The cash flow visualization is updated according to the chosen filters.
The CFO can adjust filters in real-time to refine the view.
Postconditions:
Filtered cash flows are visualized based on the selected criteria.


6. View Top Vendors and Customers
Use Case Name: View Top Vendors and Customers
Primary Actor: CFO
Goal: To allow users to view lists of the top vendors and customers based on payment amount and frequency.
Preconditions: Transaction data includes payments to vendors and from customers.
Triggers: The CFO selects the "Top Vendors and Customers" feature.
Main Success Scenario:
The CFO selects to view either top vendors or top customers.
The system retrieves the top 5 or 10 vendors/customers based on the CFOâ€™s preference.
The system displays a table with details like payment amount, frequency, and average time between payments.
The CFO can sort the data by any column (amount, frequency, etc.).
Postconditions:
The user sees the top vendors or customers in a sortable list format.


7. Visualize Cash Flow for Vendors and Customers
Use Case Name: Visualize Cash Flow for Vendors and Customers
Primary Actor: CFO
Goal: To visualize cash flows specifically for key vendors or customers.
Preconditions: Transaction data includes vendors and customers.
Triggers: The CFO selects to visualize cash flows for vendors or customers.
Main Success Scenario:
The CFO selects either "Vendors" or "Customers" from the visualization options.
The system filters and displays only transactions related to the selected vendors or customers.
The CFO can overlay additional information such as the average time between payments and payment frequency.
Postconditions:
The user sees a visualized representation of cash flows for key vendors or customers.

